Class TextElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ethanzeigler.jgamegui.element.AbstractElement
      • com.ethanzeigler.jgamegui.element.TextElement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable

    public class TextElement
extends AbstractElement
    An AbstractElement that represents text drawn on the screen with the lower-right corner of the Element as the drawing origin.

    • Constructor Detail

      • TextElement

        public TextElement(double xOrig,
                   double yOrig,
                   int priority,
                   java.lang.String text)
        Represents written text on the screen. This Element's origin is on the bottom right, not the top right like other Elements. This is due to the behavior of the Swing API.
        Parameters:
        xOrig - x origin, the leftmost point
        yOrig - y origin, the bottommost point
        priority - the draw priority
        text - the text to be drawn
